    soilAmendmentPara: "Twin Cities soils are Des Moines Lobe glacial till with Platteville limestone shelf affecting Ramsey County excavations. Northern suburbs sit on saturated Anoka Sand Plain. Malcolm's Organic Compost and SCS Field Services amendments dominate the Twin Cities market. University of Minnesota Soil Testing Lab ($17-$35) provides the baseline. Acidic conifer-canopy soils in pine-heavy lots require lime before lawn establishment. Expanded shale amendments address clay-heavy lots. Fall compost application is standard practice before winter dormancy.",
